---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import ManufacturerNote from '../../components/ManufacturerNote.astro';
import EditorialImage from '../../components/EditorialImage.astro';
import ConsultationCTA from '../../components/ConsultationCTA.astro';

const title = 'Hair Extension Colours — 141 Professional Shades';
const description =
  '141 hair extension colours from Sach & Vogue Hair — pigment-based professional colouring, natural shades, balayage, custom matching, and salon consultation support.';
const breadcrumbs = [{ label: 'Hair Extension Colours' }];
---

<BaseLayout {title} {description} path="/hair-extension-colours/" {breadcrumbs}>
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="container">
      <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs} />
      <h1>Hair extension colours</h1>
      <p class="section__lead">
        141 professional shades produced with pigment-based colouring — structured for salon consultation, reorder consistency, and every extension method we manufacture.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--compact">
    <div class="container article-body">
      <EditorialImage
        src="/images/hair-extension-colour-ring.webp"
        alt="Professional hair extension colour ring displaying a full spectrum of 141 salon shades"
        width={1448}
        height={1086}
        class="editorial-image--inline"
      />
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Colour consistency defines extension credibility. Sach &amp; Vogue Hair maintains a structured library of 141 shades spanning natural bases, cool and warm undertones, rooted formats, balayage blends, and select fashion tones. Because we manufacture in-house, shade batches are documented to support reliable reorders for salons, wholesale clients, and private label brands.</p>

        <h2>How our colour library is organised</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Natural bases</strong> — black through light blonde in warm, neutral, and ash families.</li>
          <li><strong>Rooted &amp; dimensional</strong> — pre-blended root depth for low-maintenance grow-out.</li>
          <li><strong>Balayage &amp; painted</strong> — multi-tone wefts and tips for lived-in colour results.</li>
          <li><strong>Fashion &amp; vivid</strong> — selective shades for creative and editorial styling.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="colour-swatches" aria-hidden="true">
          <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
          <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
        </div>

        <ManufacturerNote title="Professional pigments, not improvised toning">
          <p>Our colour work uses professional pigments with batch discipline — the foundation of private label stability and wholesale reorder trust. Shade drift between production runs is a manufacturing failure, not an acceptable variance.</p>
        </ManufacturerNote>

        <h2>Custom colour matching</h2>
        <p>When a client&apos;s hair falls between standard shades, our team produces custom matches from reference photos, swatches, or posted hair samples. Matching should reference daylight — not warm indoor salon lighting alone.</p>

        <h2>Women Topper colour work</h2>
        <p>Topper units require precise blending at the parting and perimeter. We apply the same shade discipline used across Tape-In, Keratin, Weft, and Clip-In lines.</p>

        <h2>Authority guide</h2>
        <p>For full colour code logic, consultation workflow, and the difference between codes like #1B and #1, read our dedicated guide:</p>
        <p><a href="/hair-extension-colours-colour-code-guide/" class="text-link">Hair Extension Colours &amp; Colour Code Guide</a></p>

        <p>Related: <a href="/the-dna-of-sach-hair-extensions/">The DNA of Sach Hair Extensions</a> · <a href="/private-label-hair-extensions/">Private label</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <ConsultationCTA heading="Need a custom match?" text="Send your colour brief via WhatsApp with method, length, and daylight reference images." />
</BaseLayout>
